name: endopeptidase La
reaction: Hydrolysis of proteins in presence of ATP
comment: Product of the lon gene in Escherichia coli. ATP hydrolysis is linked with peptide bond hydrolysis; vanadate inhibits both reactions. Type example of peptidase family S16. A similar enzyme occurs in animal mitochondria

references.title: Demonstration of an ATP-dependent, vanadate-sensitive endoprotease in the matrix of rat liver mitochondria.
Studies of the ATP-dependent proteolytic enzyme, protease La, from Escherichia coli.
Sequence of the lon gene in Escherichia coli. A heat-shock gene which encodes the ATP-dependent protease La.
